#compdef mdbook-katex
# Documentation: https://github.com/lzanini/mdbook-katex
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-17
# Verified: lzanini/mdbook-katex upstream — mdBook preprocessor
# that pre-renders LaTeX to HTML via KaTeX at build time. Tiny
# CLI: `supports RENDERER` is the only subcommand (used by mdBook
# itself), plus -h/--help and -V/--version. All configuration is
# in book.toml under [preprocessor.katex].
# Removed from prior file: bogus man.archlinux.org search URL.

local ret=1
_arguments -s -S \
  '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
  '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[show version]' \
  '1:command:(supports)' \
  '2:renderer name:(html)' && ret=0
return ret
